<br>
1. hit yourself if in a small room<br>
2. hit mezzed mobs<br>
3. have a mob move out from under it<br>
it's also evo based, so i would imagine it's off-spec for most magicians.<br>
<br>
given the potential trouble with using it i would think it should be better than DD's on single mobs, not the same.  certainly much better if you do get 2 mobs, though in pop if you have 2 mobs not mezzed in a group-xp situation you're already in trouble most times.<br>
<br>
the only reason to cast a spell that may or may not hit (either rains or bolts) is that if it does connect it is consistently better than the current DD.  harder to use for same effect is broken, that was what i was trying to say.  not that rains do less damage overall, but that they do same or slightly less when they should consistently do more than DD's if they are hitting.<br>
<br>
DD's are the bread and butter for any nuker in the end.  if you casted a rain in most groups, and every raid, odds are you are gonna be breaking mezzes..which rules rains out.  since raids are situational (situation being that you have one mob in camp and nothing else close by) they should be overall better than DD's on that single mob, not the same or worse.<br>
<br>
with sunstorm, if all 3 waves hit you are slightly ahead of black steel.  if 2 hit it's a little worse that black steel.  i can't think of a single group in pop so far where i've been able to AE 2+ mobs.  i'll even ignore the times only 1 hits, or even all resists.  if you say the 2-hit and 3-hit ones are about even then it would average out to about the same as black steel.  coming back to the point that you have a situational spell, only useful under certain conditions, that on average does the same damage as a spell you can always use anywhere. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aquaminismallwater>Aquamini Smallwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(1/20/03 9:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1787.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   /agree</span><hr size=1> Im the kinda mage that will stack 3 rains and 2 dots on a kill. in the last 10% of an Agnar fight im screwed and have to use Ancient: Shock of Sun Im ok with this. Ive done more than 10% on him total so thats my part.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hobiewankenobe>Hobiewankenobe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://myweb.thump.net/1363/pictures/Gonn.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 531<br> <font color=#333333>(1/20/03 11:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1787.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://myweb.thump.net/1363/pictures/Gonn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEI