<br>
A month an a half later pets no longer took up a wave but nothing was done about the resist rate.  <br>
<br>
First I never cast a rain without a debuff but I certainly will cast a DD without one.  So even if all waves were to hit the extra cost of debuff nullifies this efficiency.  <br>
<br>
Second, the unpredictability of the resists is unacceptable.  This coupled with all the other negatives makes the use of rains ineffective the vast majority of the time.<br>
<br>
Third, Focus items don't work with them.  Although you can get crits the infrequency and the greater resists makes that a non-issue.<br>
<br>
I never use them except to screw around.  I really can think of no reason to use them over a tried and true DD nuke.  Would I use them if the resist rate was less?  Yes I would find more times to use them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2725<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 7:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1787.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: rains</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So even if all waves were to hit the extra cost of debuff nullifies this efficiency. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If you only account for the one rain hitting, perhaps.  But <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Malosini</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is one of the best line of spells we have.  As a rule of thumb, I always <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Malosini</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> nigh everything I come across.  Even if it saves just one or two resists per fight, it is worth it.  It also increases the damage your pet does through procs, the chance that root will stick, etc.  In a group, it helps the spells of all other members.<br>
